	atFunctions, Version 3.3

		Install Notes

This document describes how to build and install atFunctions package.

1. Edit "Imakefile.def" to fit your system. 

  Read comment lines carefully and set keywords properly.

2. Make atFunctions package

  Type as follows.

	% xmkmf -a
	% make

3. Install atFunctions package

  Create install directories where you wrote in "Imakefile.def"
  (INSTALL_LIB_PATH), and type 'make install'.

  After installing atFunctions package, you can erase object files
  and libraries by typing 'make clean'.
